  "@type": "SoftwareSourceCode",
  "identifier": "arsbridge",
  "description": "Reads a lead programmer's already-annotated TLF shell Word document and the study's ADaM specification Excel, and produces a valid CDISC Analysis Results Standard (ARS) v1.0 ARM-TS JSON file suitable for consumption by 'siera::readARS()'. Annotation extraction is style-agnostic: detects ADaM variable references whether marked by font colour, character formatting, brackets, or plain-text appended after the stub label. An LLM ('ellmer'; Anthropic, OpenAI, Gemini, or an OpenAI-compatible provider such as GLM) acts as the primary reader of variant shell layouts, separating display label from variable reference, and also supplies light semantic enrichment per TLF section (analysis type, method name, row roles). Every LLM-proposed variable is gated against the ADaM specification, so an out-of-spec proposal is rejected and flagged rather than shipped; with no API key the reader degrades to deterministic parsing.",
  "name": "arsbridge: Convert Annotated TLF Shells and ADaM Spec to CDISC ARS JSON",
  "codeRepository": "https://github.com/tavakohr/arsbridge",
